    <stitle>MOR/RYDE RUBBER SPRING SUSPENSION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s03009" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5177" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>MOR/RYDE RUBBER SPRING SUSPENSION</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>MOR/RYDE</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <vendcodegroup/>

                <vendcode>03097</vendcode>
                <vendcode>03098</vendcode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>MOR/RYDE rubber spring rear axle suspension system (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300901">Figure 1</hotlnk>) provides a smoother ride, improved braking and
                        better handling than that provided by a typical leaf spring suspension.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300901" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300901" filename="../figg03/G0300901.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. MOR/RYDE RUBBER SUSPENSION SYSTEM (OCTOBER, 1986 TO PRESENT)</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1.HANGER ASSEMBLY (RIGHT REAR)</callout1>
                            <callout1>2.BOLT, .50-13 X 1.75 (FLAT HEAD GRADE 8)</callout1>
                            <callout1>3.CROSSMEMBER STRAP</callout1>
                            <callout1>4.HANGER ASSEMBLY (LEFT REAR)</callout1>
                            <callout1>5.SHOCK FASTENER</callout1>
                            <callout1>6.SHOCK ABSORBER</callout1>
                            <callout1>7.RUBBER SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>8.BOLT, .75-10 X 3.60 (HEX HEAD)</callout1>
                            <callout1>9.TRAC BAR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>10.NUT, .75-10 (HEX LOCK)</callout1>
                            <callout1>11.U-BOLT NUT</callout1>
                            <callout1>12.U-BOLT</callout1>
                            <callout1>13.AXLE PAD ADJUSTMENT SEAT</callout1>
                            <callout1>14.BOTTOM U-BOLT CASTING</callout1>
                            <callout1>15.AXLE PAD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>16.BEAM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>17.HANGER ASSEMBLY (LEFT FRONT)</callout1>
                            <callout1>18.TRAC BAR ADJUSTMENT WITH NUT</callout1>
                            <callout1>19.BOLT, .75-10 X 3.50 (ALLEN HEAD)</callout1>
                            <callout1>20.HANGER ASSEMBLY (RIGHT FRONT)</callout1>
                            <callout1>21.FRAME SWAY BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>22.SWAY BRACKET-INSIDE FLANGE BRACE</callout1>
                            <callout1>23.SPACER .25 X 1.0 X 1.0</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The springs are made of a special formulation of natural rubber that is vulcanized (bonded) to
                        steel plates. Metal never contacts metal so less frictional force is created. This design
                        assures that the force of road bumps is more readily absorbed providing smoother ride and
                        passenger comfort. The rubber springs also increase a vehicle's wheel-to-road contact which
                        improves braking.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The rubber springs are positioned in line with the wheels. This provides greater vehicle
                        stability, better handling and driveability, and increased driver control.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The suspension system incorporates a trac bar to keep the drive wheels parallel with the
                        centerline of vehicle. The beam assembly attaches to the chassis side-members fore and aft
                        without a slip joint which greatly reduces roll steering.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
